article.headline: Youngstown State 81, Wisconsin-Milwaukee 63
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Quin Humphrey scored 22 points and had 11 rebounds and Keston Roberts keyed a 15-5 run late in the first half to lead Youngstown State to an 81-63 victory over Wisconsin-Milwaukee Saturday night. Humphrey's 3-pointer tied the game at 18 with 5:47 left in the first half, then Roberts scored five of Youngstown State's next 12 to give the Penguins (8-10, 3-3 Horizon League) a 30-23 lead at the half. Youngstown State's lead expanded to 48-35 on Jack Liles' layup with 12:49 left. The Panthers (5-14, 2-4) pulled to 50-43 on Kevin Massiah's jumper with 10:33 remaining but got no closer. Byron Davis added 17 for the Penguins and Roberts finished with 14. Ricky Franklin had 18 points for Wisconsin-Milwaukee and Massiah added 11.
